creator: acoamorim@gmail.com
text:
Environment: Debian 3.1r1, Apache 2, PHP5.

Symptom: Try acess default URL of site. PHP script not run. A save dialog box is
showed. Msg from mozzila: " ... i don't know application/x-trash ...". Apache
conf files verifieds and Ok. PHP module Ok.

Cause: index.html.bak presents on /var/www. Erase or rename this with no html
extension. Problem solved.

It´s a very difult to find error. Many questions found in forums.

creator: slive@apache.org
text: *** Bug 39132 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

Please address this question on a user-support forum like the
users@httpd.apache.org mailing list.  It is almost certainly a configuration
error and not a bug.  It is also possible that Debian is using a confusing
default configuration, but you should address that in the Debian bug database,
not here.
creator: slive@apache.org
